oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Panoramic photograh of Supply Co., 114th FA, 30th Division
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: 114th FA was part of the 30th Division. The 30th Div. was composed primarily of National Guard units from Tennessee and the Carolinas. The Division came into existence at Camp Sevier, South Carolina in 1918. The photograph shows mule drawn supply wagons. The officers appear on horses and the enlisted men are standing in line. The image belonged to 1st Class Machinist Robert Jackson and he is presumed to be in the image. Jackson was born in Dekalb County but lived most of his life in Wilson County, Tenn.
